 multiculturalism; and the relationship between diasporic identities and claims to space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSociologie urbainexCanada. 0aSociology, UrbanxCanada. 0aSociology, UrbanzCanada. 4aSocial Science: Sociology. 4aSocial Science: Urban Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aTeelucksingh, Cheryl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458137540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581375423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554581375/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles